# Copy to ".env.local" for local development. Never commit real secrets.
#
# Security (public GitHub repo): only use VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (anon) in Vite — never the
# service_role key or Stripe/Anthropic secrets here; those belong in Supabase Edge secrets only.

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE (dashboard, auth, workflows, Ask Nora backend URL)
# =============================================================================
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Dashboard “Content Agent” runs call the Edge Function `nora-workflow` with the signed-in user’s JWT.
# In Supabase → Project Settings → Edge Functions → Secrets, set:
#   LOVABLE_API_KEY   — required for AI generation (Lovable AI gateway)
# Functions also receive SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY automatically.
# See supabase/config.toml: nora-workflow has verify_jwt = true.
#
# Optional — extra accounts that skip the public 3/day Nora chat cap and workflow user rate cap (comma-separated):
#   Local Vite:  VITE_NORA_UNLIMITED_EMAILS=you@example.com
#   Edge secrets: supabase secrets set NORA_UNLIMITED_EMAILS=you@example.com
# Built-in founder list is in supabase/functions/_shared/noraQuota.ts and src/config/noraQuota.ts.

# =============================================================================
# CLAUDE (Anthropic) — LOCAL ONLY with npm run dev
# =============================================================================
# The Vite dev server reads CLAUDE_API_KEY and exposes POST /api/claude (see vite/plugin-claude-api.ts).
# Your key never goes into the JavaScript bundle.
CLAUDE_API_KEY=
# Optional model override (default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514). Legacy: ANTHROPIC_MODEL still works.
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514

# Use Claude for Ask Nora (local dev). For the public GitHub Pages build, leave this as ollama or unset.
VITE_AI_PROVIDER=ollama

# =============================================================================
# GITHUB PAGES + GITHUB ACTIONS
# =============================================================================
# Required for any production build (including CI): the Vite bundle must receive these at
# `npm run build` time. For GitHub Pages, add them as repository Variables (not Secrets):
#   Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables
#     VITE_SUPABASE_URL              = https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
#     VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY  = <anon public key from Supabase Dashboard → API>
# The workflow `.github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml` passes vars.VITE_* into the build.
#
# GitHub Pages only serves static files from dist/. There is NO server for your API key on Pages.
#
# A repo Secret named CLAUDE_API_KEY is NOT visible to the live site or to `vite build` unless you
# wrongly expose it (e.g. VITE_*), which would leak the key in public JavaScript. Do not do that.
#
# To use Claude on the deployed site (step-by-step, Supabase — same project as waitlist):
#
# 1) Install CLI: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/cli
#    Link (once):  supabase link --project-ref bblzvdfztnxrebfupjtj
#
# 2) Put the Anthropic key on Supabase (never in the repo):
#      supabase secrets set CLAUDE_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-...
#    Optional:     supabase secrets set CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514
#
# 3) Deploy the proxy in this repo:
#      supabase functions deploy nora-claude
#    (verify_jwt = false for this function is set in supabase/config.toml so the Pages site can call it.)
#
# 4) GitHub → repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables → New variable:
#      Name:  VITE_AI_PROVIDER          Value: claude
#      Name:  VITE_CLAUDE_API_BASE      Value: https://bblzvdfztnxrebfupjtj.supabase.co/functions/v1/nora-claude
#    Replace the host with your project ref from Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API if different.
#
# 5) Push to main so “Deploy GitHub Pages” rebuilds with those variables.
#
# The GitHub secret CLAUDE_API_KEY is unused by this flow; the key lives only in Supabase secrets.
# This endpoint is public — monitor Anthropic usage and add rate limiting / auth if traffic grows.
#
# Practical setup:
# - Live site with Ollama: leave VITE_AI_PROVIDER unset or ollama (Ollama still only works locally
#   with npm run dev + ollama serve — visitors cannot reach your laptop).
# - Claude on your laptop: .env.local + CLAUDE_API_KEY + VITE_AI_PROVIDER=claude + npm run dev

# Optional Ollama
# VITE_OLLAMA_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:11434

# =============================================================================
# STRIPE (subscriptions — secrets only on Supabase Edge Functions, not Vite)
# =============================================================================
# Set via: supabase secrets set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
#          supabase secrets set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
#          supabase secrets set STRIPE_PRICE_PLUS=price_...
#          supabase secrets set STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...
# Optional: STRIPE_PORTAL_CONFIGURATION_ID (Billing portal configuration ID from Stripe Dashboard)
# Optional: APP_URL=https://your-production-domain.com (Checkout / portal return URLs)
#
# Payment Links (public — safe as Vite env). Defaults match production links; override if you change them in Stripe.
#   VITE_STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK_PLUS=https://buy.stripe.com/...
#   VITE_STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK_PRO=https://buy.stripe.com/...
# STRIPE_PRICE_PLUS / STRIPE_PRICE_PRO must be the Price IDs (price_...) on those links so the webhook sets Plus vs Pro correctly.
#
# After deploying stripe-webhook, register webhook URL in Stripe Dashboard:
#   https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/functions/v1/stripe-webhook
#
# App URL for Checkout return (also set as Edge secret if functions need it):
#   APP_URL=https://xenoraai.com
